@* This exemplar ingestion rule editor proves the Search module can contribute a second lightweight planning surface through the same singleton activation policy. *@
<section class="ingestion-rule-editor-tool" aria-labelledby="ingestion-rule-editor-tool-title">
    <header class="ingestion-rule-editor-tool__header">
        <p class="ingestion-rule-editor-tool__eyebrow">Search module</p>
        <h1 id="ingestion-rule-editor-tool-title">Ingestion rule editor</h1>
        <p>
            This dummy rule-editing surface reserves space for future rule authoring workflows while validating
            explorer placement, bounded tool activation, and active-tool status-bar participation.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="ingestion-rule-editor-tool__content">
        <section>
            <h2>Planned rule-editing focus</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Inspect rule definitions and author rule changes through the Workbench shell.</li>
                <li>Surface validation and publish status through bounded runtime shell contributions.</li>
                <li>Share Search module services while remaining independently openable from the explorer.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Current fixed Workbench context</h2>
            <dl class="ingestion-rule-editor-tool__context-list">
                @foreach (var contextEntry in ContextValues)
                {
                    <div>
                        <dt>@contextEntry.Key</dt>
                        <dd>@(string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(contextEntry.Value) ? "(empty)" : contextEntry.Value)</dd>
                    </div>
                }
            </dl>
        </section>
    </div>
</section>
